Thank you for the report. I could only reproduce the issue with my project owner session, the maintainer always gets this error.

```json
{
  "data": {
    "destroySnippet": null
  },
  "errors": [
    {
      "message": "The resource that you are attempting to access does not exist or you don't have permission to perform this action",
      "locations": [
        {
          "line": 2,
          "column": 3
        }
      ],
      "path": [
        "destroySnippet"
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

Can you confirm that you are really able to do this with the maintainer user?

Thank you,
Dominic
GitLab Security Team

Yes I'm pretty sure i still can.
For simplicity please use the following payload as Maintainer of the project

```
mutation test{
  destroySnippet(input: {id: "gid://gitlab/Project/<id>"}){
    errors
  }
}
```

with ID as the Project ID you been added as Maintainer
